This paper deals with propositional logic for reasoning about expectation, which is a central notion in probability theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which includes topics related to probabilistic reasoning and decision-making. The paper also discusses axiomatizations for different representations of uncertainty, such as sets of probability measures, belief functions, and possibility measures, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also involves the use of logic, which is relevant to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
